## TL;DR: What Every Lab Grown Cushion Cut Buyer Must Know First

The lab grown cushion cut diamond is the single highest-value purchase in the engagement ring market in {{year}}. Not because it is cheaper — though it is, dramatically — but because at 2ct and above, the price difference between lab and natural is so extreme that buying natural requires a specific philosophical justification that most buyers cannot honestly provide.

**Contrarian Truth — The Modified Brilliant Split:** Not all lab grown cushion cut diamonds look the same. Blue Nile lists two distinct cushion sub-types: the cushion modified brilliant (crushed ice pattern — dense, uniform sparkle) and the cushion brilliant (chunkier traditional facets — larger flashes, more fire). GIA and IGI certificates describe the cut type in a single line that most buyers overlook entirely. Buying the wrong sub-type is the most common mistake lab cushion buyers make, and no retailer's product photo reliably distinguishes between them.

**Live price snapshot (Blue Nile {{year}}):**
- Lab 1.5ct IGI E-VVS2 Excellent Cushion Modified: **[$1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Lab 2ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Lab 3ct GIA D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Natural 2ct GIA F-VVS2 Ideal Cushion Modified (equivalent): **[$13,679](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29359194?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**→ The best entry point** for most buyers is the [IGI 2ct D-VVS1 Ideal Cut Cushion Modified at $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the crushed ice modified brilliant at 2ct delivers a face-up size that looks significantly larger than a 1ct on the hand, D colour is the absolute top, VVS1 clarity is genuinely clean, and $2,606 for this combination is impossible in the natural market. The natural equivalent at this quality grade is approximately $16,000.

